-- Greek Banks’ Capital Plans Set for April 20, Papademos Says
-- B y   S t e l i o s   O r p h a n i d e s
-- 2012-04-06T07:52:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-06/greek-banks-capital-plans-set-for-april-20-papademos-says.html
Greek banks’ plans for raising extra
capital to cover losses from the country’s debt swap with
private investors will be announced by April 20, Greek Prime
Minister  Lucas Papademos  said.  The process of recapitalizing the banks will need to be
completed by September, Papademos told reporters in Nicosia
yesterday on a visit to Cyprus.  To contact the reporter on this story:
